            <fr:title text="Section-retraction pair">Section-retraction pair</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>section-retraction pair</fr:strong></fr:em> is defined to be a pair of <fr:link href="jms-00KF.xml" title="Function" addr="jms-00KF" type="local">functions</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\colon  B \to  A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\circ  s =\mathsf {id}_{B}]]></fr:tex>. In this case, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> is referred to as a <fr:em><fr:strong>section</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> is referred to as a <fr:em><fr:strong>retraction</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
